included.title: Design Researcher

included.summary:
"Research is formalized curiosity. It is poking and prying with a purpose." - Zora Neale Hurston

I'm a qualitative UX Researcher passionate about understanding human behavior to help design products and services that matter. 

I have experience evaluating user experiences across digital and physical product spaces. I'm comfortable with research and testing across the product development spectrum from "phase zero" generative research to nitty-gritty usability testing. 

Methodologies:
* Design thinking
* Interviews (remote and in-person)
* Usability testing (remote, in-person, and guerrilla)
* Surveys and site intercepts
* Persona creation
* Journey mapping
* Contextual inquiry/ethnographic research
* Co-creation design activities
* Card sorts
* Diary studies
* Competitive analysis
* UX audits
